# QA Demo Project - Common Testing Rules

## Project Overview

Full-stack Task Management app demonstrating the testing pyramid:
- Backend: SpringBoot + MongoDB + Kafka
- Frontend: React + TypeScript
- Testing: Unit, Integration, Component, Contract (Pact), E2E (Playwright)

## Rules (All Test Types)

- Name tests `should<Behavior>When<Condition>`; use Given-When-Then comments
- Avoid adding extra comments to the code, the code should be clean enough to read it without comments
- Avoid static waiters (setTimeout, Thread.sleep) — wait for an actual condition instead (waitFor(), await(), awaitility)
- Avoid logic in tests (loops, conditionals); use test parametrisation instead

## General Guidelines

- **Shift-Left Testing:** Prioritize unit and integration tests over E2E tests
- **Testing Pyramid:** Most tests at unit level → fewer at integration → minimal at E2E
